text: Oran Beecher Davis (April 25, 1872 – May 16, 1960) was a Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick as member of the Liberal party representing Victoria County from 1925 to 1930. ==References== Category:20th-century Canadian politicians Category:1872 births Category:1960 deaths Category:New Brunswick Liberal Association MLAs
